      "content": "i get what you're saying but it just doesn't feel like there's anything left to mend. even if i talked to someone, the person they'd be talking to is just the \"actor\" i mentioned. the actual person is just... gone. it feels more like accepting a fact than a problem to be solved. like, if you realize a character in a play isn't real, you don't try to fix the character, you just stop playing.",
